category.name: religion/beliefs
description:
Welcome to Stockholm Skeptic Discussions!

PLEASE NOTE: Skepticism doesn't mean being arbitrary "sceptical". A skeptic, or "freethinker" is one who prefers beliefs and conclusions that are reliable and valid to ones that are personally comforting or convenient (such as religion, conspiracy theories, alternative medicine, spiritual healing or anything "supernatural"). Skepticism is not an ideology or a belief system. Skepticism is a methodology for learning about and understanding the world based on the scientific method. To learn more, please watch this short video: "What is a Skeptic?", and preferably also "Why people believe weird things", both by Michael Shermer of The Sceptic Society (USA).

This group is for people who want to discuss and learn about the world in accordance to this methodology (including, but not limited to conversations about science, pseudo-science, philosophy, atheism, secular ethics, evolution and humanism) with like-minded people in the Stockholm area. 

No merits are required apart from respecting that. We all have to start somewhere :)

Hope to see you there!

PS: If you want to read more, and better understand terminology we may use on the meetups, we have more resources and links listed here.

Rules: Don't be condescending or otherwise aggressive. A necessary part of being a skeptic is questioning your own stances, being able to handle critique and letting others speak. Even if you're "sure" you're right (which you shouldn't be), we are not organizing these events to listen to someone's agenda. We're here to participate in discussions where scientific and rational arguments trumps attitude. Sexism and racism also is strictly forbidden.
name: Stockholm Skeptic Discussions

description: Wat Phra Dhammakaya Stockholm in Stora Vika provides Mindfulness training through the Middle Way Meditation technique. We serve people of all ages, races, nationalities, religions and faiths who have intention to develop the inner peace, stress-free state of the mind, genuine happiness and harmony among family members. We offers meditation and educational training programs, based on mental and spiritual confluence, and organization of various cultural activities to promote unity and harmony among all. Our ultimate aim is to promote peace and happiness in people’s lives by using the technique which is simple, effective for self-discovery and enhance purification of the mind.

description:
Vi är Buddhistiska gemenskapen, Karme Tenpe Gyaltsen (KTG). Hos oss kan du lära dig buddhistisk meditation och ta del av föredrag och undervisning inom Karma kagyu buddhismen, den muntligt överförda traditionen.

Panchen Lama som en reinkarnation av den berömda retreatmästaren Tshampa Rinpoche från Yangpachen i Tibet. Han bor och verkar nu i Sverige och leder verksamheten i stort.

description:
This is a group with focus on the real world. That will produce a dictionary to use when you want to call things for what they are. That help you root out all those words with religious connotations from your language.

Why give religion credibility by using words that carry their agenda? Isn’t it about time you stop doing that?

Take the expression 'to desecrate' for example. It is said that you can do this to a church. Which is strange. Because if you piss you piss. Right? No matter if it’s on Skatteverket, a church or Trump Tower. Desecrate? Yeah yeah… Or look at the word soul. Please define it. Do you find it difficult? Well, I say it’s since it’s concocted. Fiction. Made up. And what is holy really? Join and let’s find out!
name: Secular Dictionary Production With Big Mary

category.name: religion/beliefs
description:
Open for everyone that feels like there could be more to life than just what our eyes can see and our minds contemplate! Starting sometime in February or march - We will do a course that will run for 7 weeks from our home in Kärrtorp, exploring life through the christian faith. We aim to host it in a low-key easy style; where no questions are considered in appropriate and no one should feel unwelcomed.

The outline of the course is as follows:
Session 1 The Good God
Session 2 The Trustworthy God
Session 3 The Generous God
Session 4 The Liberating God
Session 5 The Fulfilling God
Session 6 The Life-Giving God
Session 7 The Joyful God

Welcome - wether saint, heretic, skeptic, seeker, agnostic or believer... every one can come no matter where you are on your spiritual journey!
Peace & Love: Anna & Samuel

-------

Öppen för alla som känner att det kan vara mer till livet än vad våra ögon kan se och våra förstånd säger oss! Med början någon gång i februari eller mars - kommer vi att göra en 7 veckors kurs i vårt hem i Kärrtorp, som utforskar livet genom den kristna tron. Vi strävar efter att skapa en enkel, avskalad plats; där inga frågor anses olämpliga och ingen ska känna sig ovälkommen.

Kursens upplägg:
Session 1 Den goda Guden
Session 2 Den trovärdiga Guden
Session 3 Den generösa Guden
Session 4 Den befriande Guden
Session 5 Den uppfyllande Guden
Session 6 Den livgivande Guden
Session 7 Den glädjande Guden

Oavsett var du befinner dig på din livsresa - om du är sökare, troende, skeptiker, heretiker eller ett helgon, så är du varmt välkommen!
Fred & kärlek / Anna & Samuel
name: Life & Jesus Explored - Stockholm

description: Humanisterna Syd är en lokalavdelning inom förbundet Humanisterna som geografiskt omfattar Skåne och Blekinge. Vi anordnar medlemsaktiviteter som föreläsningar, debatter, diskussions- och pubkvällar. För kontakt, maila oss på syd@humanisterna.se Förbundet Humanisterna vill främja humanismens livssyn som idé- och värdegrund för samhälle, kultur och etik. Grundläggande för humanismen är kritiskt tänkande och en vetenskaplig kunskapssyn. Humanismen är en sekulär – icke-religiös – livssyn som anser att det inte finns några förnuftiga skäl att tro på religiösa dogmer, gudar eller övernaturliga förklaringar av tillvaron. Humanismen sätter människan och människovärdet i centrum. Den förenar medmänsklighet och förnuft i en strävan att skapa ett bättre samhälle, där ansvaret läggs på människan själv. Demokrati och mänskliga rättigheter är universella värden som måste gälla alla människor, oavsett var man råkar leva.

description: Namaste ! This fraternal group invites to those open and free minds who are interested in searching the fundamental principles that are found within the world religions and metaphysical schools. We will try to understand and practice those principles from the practical point of view. Our approach is one that recognizes and values the diversity of beliefs, experiences, theories and convictions. In this way, we will not be promoting or privileging one interpretation or worldview over another, instead, we'll be looking for common bridges across religions and worldviews in order to positively impact our personal life and society through a universal spiritual revolution.

category.name: religion/beliefs
description:
Welcome to Stockholm Skeptic Discussions!

PLEASE NOTE: Skepticism doesn't mean being arbitrary "sceptical". A skeptic, or "freethinker" is one who prefers beliefs and conclusions that are reliable and valid to ones that are personally comforting or convenient (such as religion, conspiracy theories, alternative medicine, spiritual healing or anything "supernatural"). Skepticism is not an ideology or a belief system. Skepticism is a methodology for learning about and understanding the world based on the scientific method. To learn more, please watch this short video: "What is a Skeptic?", and preferably also "Why people believe weird things", both by Michael Shermer of The Sceptic Society (USA).

This group is for people who want to discuss and learn about the world in accordance to this methodology (including, but not limited to conversations about science, pseudo-science, philosophy, atheism, secular ethics, evolution and humanism) with like-minded people in the Stockholm area. 

No merits are required apart from respecting that. We all have to start somewhere :)

Hope to see you there!

PS: If you want to read more, and better understand terminology we may use on the meetups, we have more resources and links listed here.

Rules: Don't be condescending or otherwise aggressive. A necessary part of being a skeptic is questioning your own stances, being able to handle critique and letting others speak. Even if you're "sure" you're right (which you shouldn't be), we are not organizing these events to listen to someone's agenda. We're here to participate in discussions where scientific and rational arguments trumps attitude. Sexism and racism also is strictly forbidden.
name: Stockholm Skeptic Discussions

description:
This is a group with focus on the real world. That will produce a dictionary to use when you want to call things for what they are. That help you root out all those words with religious connotations from your language.

Why give religion credibility by using words that carry their agenda? Isn’t it about time you stop doing that?

Take the expression 'to desecrate' for example. It is said that you can do this to a church. Which is strange. Because if you piss you piss. Right? No matter if it’s on Skatteverket, a church or Trump Tower. Desecrate? Yeah yeah… Or look at the word soul. Please define it. Do you find it difficult? Well, I say it’s since it’s concocted. Fiction. Made up. And what is holy really? Join and let’s find out!
name: Secular Dictionary Production With Big Mary

category.name: religion/beliefs
description:
Open for everyone that feels like there could be more to life than just what our eyes can see and our minds contemplate! Starting sometime in February or march - We will do a course that will run for 7 weeks from our home in Kärrtorp, exploring life through the christian faith. We aim to host it in a low-key easy style; where no questions are considered in appropriate and no one should feel unwelcomed.

The outline of the course is as follows:
Session 1 The Good God
Session 2 The Trustworthy God
Session 3 The Generous God
Session 4 The Liberating God
Session 5 The Fulfilling God
Session 6 The Life-Giving God
Session 7 The Joyful God

Welcome - wether saint, heretic, skeptic, seeker, agnostic or believer... every one can come no matter where you are on your spiritual journey!
Peace & Love: Anna & Samuel

-------

Öppen för alla som känner att det kan vara mer till livet än vad våra ögon kan se och våra förstånd säger oss! Med början någon gång i februari eller mars - kommer vi att göra en 7 veckors kurs i vårt hem i Kärrtorp, som utforskar livet genom den kristna tron. Vi strävar efter att skapa en enkel, avskalad plats; där inga frågor anses olämpliga och ingen ska känna sig ovälkommen.

Kursens upplägg:
Session 1 Den goda Guden
Session 2 Den trovärdiga Guden
Session 3 Den generösa Guden
Session 4 Den befriande Guden
Session 5 Den uppfyllande Guden
Session 6 Den livgivande Guden
Session 7 Den glädjande Guden

Oavsett var du befinner dig på din livsresa - om du är sökare, troende, skeptiker, heretiker eller ett helgon, så är du varmt välkommen!
Fred & kärlek / Anna & Samuel
name: Life & Jesus Explored - Stockholm

category.name: religion/beliefs
description:
Open for everyone that feels like there could be more to life than just what our eyes can see and our minds contemplate! Starting sometime in February or march - We will do a course that will run for 7 weeks from our home in Kärrtorp, exploring life through the christian faith. We aim to host it in a low-key easy style; where no questions are considered in appropriate and no one should feel unwelcomed.

The outline of the course is as follows:
Session 1 The Good God
Session 2 The Trustworthy God
Session 3 The Generous God
Session 4 The Liberating God
Session 5 The Fulfilling God
Session 6 The Life-Giving God
Session 7 The Joyful God

Welcome - wether saint, heretic, skeptic, seeker, agnostic or believer... every one can come no matter where you are on your spiritual journey!
Peace & Love: Anna & Samuel

-------

Öppen för alla som känner att det kan vara mer till livet än vad våra ögon kan se och våra förstånd säger oss! Med början någon gång i februari eller mars - kommer vi att göra en 7 veckors kurs i vårt hem i Kärrtorp, som utforskar livet genom den kristna tron. Vi strävar efter att skapa en enkel, avskalad plats; där inga frågor anses olämpliga och ingen ska känna sig ovälkommen.

Kursens upplägg:
Session 1 Den goda Guden
Session 2 Den trovärdiga Guden
Session 3 Den generösa Guden
Session 4 Den befriande Guden
Session 5 Den uppfyllande Guden
Session 6 Den livgivande Guden
Session 7 Den glädjande Guden

Oavsett var du befinner dig på din livsresa - om du är sökare, troende, skeptiker, heretiker eller ett helgon, så är du varmt välkommen!
Fred & kärlek / Anna & Samuel

category.name: religion/beliefs
description:
Welcome to Stockholm Skeptic Discussions!

PLEASE NOTE: Skepticism doesn't mean being arbitrary "sceptical". A skeptic, or "freethinker" is one who prefers beliefs and conclusions that are reliable and valid to ones that are personally comforting or convenient (such as religion, conspiracy theories, alternative medicine, spiritual healing or anything "supernatural"). Skepticism is not an ideology or a belief system. Skepticism is a methodology for learning about and understanding the world based on the scientific method. To learn more, please watch this short video: "What is a Skeptic?", and preferably also "Why people believe weird things", both by Michael Shermer of The Sceptic Society (USA).

This group is for people who want to discuss and learn about the world in accordance to this methodology (including, but not limited to conversations about science, pseudo-science, philosophy, atheism, secular ethics, evolution and humanism) with like-minded people in the Stockholm area. 

No merits are required apart from respecting that. We all have to start somewhere :)

Hope to see you there!

PS: If you want to read more, and better understand terminology we may use on the meetups, we have more resources and links listed here.

Rules: Don't be condescending or otherwise aggressive. A necessary part of being a skeptic is questioning your own stances, being able to handle critique and letting others speak. Even if you're "sure" you're right (which you shouldn't be), we are not organizing these events to listen to someone's agenda. We're here to participate in discussions where scientific and rational arguments trumps attitude. Sexism and racism also is strictly forbidden.
name: Stockholm Skeptic Discussions

description: Wat Phra Dhammakaya Stockholm in Stora Vika provides Mindfulness training through the Middle Way Meditation technique. We serve people of all ages, races, nationalities, religions and faiths who have intention to develop the inner peace, stress-free state of the mind, genuine happiness and harmony among family members. We offers meditation and educational training programs, based on mental and spiritual confluence, and organization of various cultural activities to promote unity and harmony among all. Our ultimate aim is to promote peace and happiness in people’s lives by using the technique which is simple, effective for self-discovery and enhance purification of the mind.

description:
Vi är Buddhistiska gemenskapen, Karme Tenpe Gyaltsen (KTG). Hos oss kan du lära dig buddhistisk meditation och ta del av föredrag och undervisning inom Karma kagyu buddhismen, den muntligt överförda traditionen.

Panchen Lama som en reinkarnation av den berömda retreatmästaren Tshampa Rinpoche från Yangpachen i Tibet. Han bor och verkar nu i Sverige och leder verksamheten i stort.

description: Namaste ! This fraternal group invites to those open and free minds who are interested in searching the fundamental principles that are found within the world religions and metaphysical schools. We will try to understand and practice those principles from the practical point of view. Our approach is one that recognizes and values the diversity of beliefs, experiences, theories and convictions. In this way, we will not be promoting or privileging one interpretation or worldview over another, instead, we'll be looking for common bridges across religions and worldviews in order to positively impact our personal life and society through a universal spiritual revolution.

category.name: religion/beliefs
description:
This is a group with focus on the real world. That will produce a dictionary to use when you want to call things for what they are. That help you root out all those words with religious connotations from your language.

Why give religion credibility by using words that carry their agenda? Isn’t it about time you stop doing that?

Take the expression 'to desecrate' for example. It is said that you can do this to a church. Which is strange. Because if you piss you piss. Right? No matter if it’s on Skatteverket, a church or Trump Tower. Desecrate? Yeah yeah… Or look at the word soul. Please define it. Do you find it difficult? Well, I say it’s since it’s concocted. Fiction. Made up. And what is holy really? Join and let’s find out!
name: Secular Dictionary Production With Big Mary
organizer.name: Jan Åhlander

description:
This is a group with focus on the real world. That will produce a dictionary to use when you want to call things for what they are. That help you root out all those words with religious connotations from your language.

Why give religion credibility by using words that carry their agenda? Isn’t it about time you stop doing that?

Take the expression 'to desecrate' for example. It is said that you can do this to a church. Which is strange. Because if you piss you piss. Right? No matter if it’s on Skatteverket, a church or Trump Tower. Desecrate? Yeah yeah… Or look at the word soul. Please define it. Do you find it difficult? Well, I say it’s since it’s concocted. Fiction. Made up. And what is holy really? Join and let’s find out!
name: Secular Dictionary Production With Big Mary

category.name: religion/beliefs
description:
Open for everyone that feels like there could be more to life than just what our eyes can see and our minds contemplate! Starting sometime in February or march - We will do a course that will run for 7 weeks from our home in Kärrtorp, exploring life through the christian faith. We aim to host it in a low-key easy style; where no questions are considered in appropriate and no one should feel unwelcomed.

The outline of the course is as follows:
Session 1 The Good God
Session 2 The Trustworthy God
Session 3 The Generous God
Session 4 The Liberating God
Session 5 The Fulfilling God
Session 6 The Life-Giving God
Session 7 The Joyful God

Welcome - wether saint, heretic, skeptic, seeker, agnostic or believer... every one can come no matter where you are on your spiritual journey!
Peace & Love: Anna & Samuel

-------

Öppen för alla som känner att det kan vara mer till livet än vad våra ögon kan se och våra förstånd säger oss! Med början någon gång i februari eller mars - kommer vi att göra en 7 veckors kurs i vårt hem i Kärrtorp, som utforskar livet genom den kristna tron. Vi strävar efter att skapa en enkel, avskalad plats; där inga frågor anses olämpliga och ingen ska känna sig ovälkommen.

Kursens upplägg:
Session 1 Den goda Guden
Session 2 Den trovärdiga Guden
Session 3 Den generösa Guden
Session 4 Den befriande Guden
Session 5 Den uppfyllande Guden
Session 6 Den livgivande Guden
Session 7 Den glädjande Guden

Oavsett var du befinner dig på din livsresa - om du är sökare, troende, skeptiker, heretiker eller ett helgon, så är du varmt välkommen!
Fred & kärlek / Anna & Samuel
name: Life & Jesus Explored - Stockholm

description: Humanisterna Syd är en lokalavdelning inom förbundet Humanisterna som geografiskt omfattar Skåne och Blekinge. Vi anordnar medlemsaktiviteter som föreläsningar, debatter, diskussions- och pubkvällar. För kontakt, maila oss på syd@humanisterna.se Förbundet Humanisterna vill främja humanismens livssyn som idé- och värdegrund för samhälle, kultur och etik. Grundläggande för humanismen är kritiskt tänkande och en vetenskaplig kunskapssyn. Humanismen är en sekulär – icke-religiös – livssyn som anser att det inte finns några förnuftiga skäl att tro på religiösa dogmer, gudar eller övernaturliga förklaringar av tillvaron. Humanismen sätter människan och människovärdet i centrum. Den förenar medmänsklighet och förnuft i en strävan att skapa ett bättre samhälle, där ansvaret läggs på människan själv. Demokrati och mänskliga rättigheter är universella värden som måste gälla alla människor, oavsett var man råkar leva.
name: Humanisterna Syd

category.name: religion/beliefs
description:
Welcome to Stockholm Skeptic Discussions!

PLEASE NOTE: Skepticism doesn't mean being arbitrary "sceptical". A skeptic, or "freethinker" is one who prefers beliefs and conclusions that are reliable and valid to ones that are personally comforting or convenient (such as religion, conspiracy theories, alternative medicine, spiritual healing or anything "supernatural"). Skepticism is not an ideology or a belief system. Skepticism is a methodology for learning about and understanding the world based on the scientific method. To learn more, please watch this short video: "What is a Skeptic?", and preferably also "Why people believe weird things", both by Michael Shermer of The Sceptic Society (USA).

This group is for people who want to discuss and learn about the world in accordance to this methodology (including, but not limited to conversations about science, pseudo-science, philosophy, atheism, secular ethics, evolution and humanism) with like-minded people in the Stockholm area. 

No merits are required apart from respecting that. We all have to start somewhere :)

Hope to see you there!

PS: If you want to read more, and better understand terminology we may use on the meetups, we have more resources and links listed here.

Rules: Don't be condescending or otherwise aggressive. A necessary part of being a skeptic is questioning your own stances, being able to handle critique and letting others speak. Even if you're "sure" you're right (which you shouldn't be), we are not organizing these events to listen to someone's agenda. We're here to participate in discussions where scientific and rational arguments trumps attitude. Sexism and racism also is strictly forbidden.

category.name: religion/beliefs
description:
Open for everyone that feels like there could be more to life than just what our eyes can see and our minds contemplate! Starting sometime in February or march - We will do a course that will run for 7 weeks from our home in Kärrtorp, exploring life through the christian faith. We aim to host it in a low-key easy style; where no questions are considered in appropriate and no one should feel unwelcomed.

The outline of the course is as follows:
Session 1 The Good God
Session 2 The Trustworthy God
Session 3 The Generous God
Session 4 The Liberating God
Session 5 The Fulfilling God
Session 6 The Life-Giving God
Session 7 The Joyful God

Welcome - wether saint, heretic, skeptic, seeker, agnostic or believer... every one can come no matter where you are on your spiritual journey!
Peace & Love: Anna & Samuel

-------

Öppen för alla som känner att det kan vara mer till livet än vad våra ögon kan se och våra förstånd säger oss! Med början någon gång i februari eller mars - kommer vi att göra en 7 veckors kurs i vårt hem i Kärrtorp, som utforskar livet genom den kristna tron. Vi strävar efter att skapa en enkel, avskalad plats; där inga frågor anses olämpliga och ingen ska känna sig ovälkommen.

Kursens upplägg:
Session 1 Den goda Guden
Session 2 Den trovärdiga Guden
Session 3 Den generösa Guden
Session 4 Den befriande Guden
Session 5 Den uppfyllande Guden
Session 6 Den livgivande Guden
Session 7 Den glädjande Guden

Oavsett var du befinner dig på din livsresa - om du är sökare, troende, skeptiker, heretiker eller ett helgon, så är du varmt välkommen!
Fred & kärlek / Anna & Samuel

category.name: religion/beliefs
description: Humanisterna Syd är en lokalavdelning inom förbundet Humanisterna som geografiskt omfattar Skåne och Blekinge. Vi anordnar medlemsaktiviteter som föreläsningar, debatter, diskussions- och pubkvällar. För kontakt, maila oss på syd@humanisterna.se Förbundet Humanisterna vill främja humanismens livssyn som idé- och värdegrund för samhälle, kultur och etik. Grundläggande för humanismen är kritiskt tänkande och en vetenskaplig kunskapssyn. Humanismen är en sekulär – icke-religiös – livssyn som anser att det inte finns några förnuftiga skäl att tro på religiösa dogmer, gudar eller övernaturliga förklaringar av tillvaron. Humanismen sätter människan och människovärdet i centrum. Den förenar medmänsklighet och förnuft i en strävan att skapa ett bättre samhälle, där ansvaret läggs på människan själv. Demokrati och mänskliga rättigheter är universella värden som måste gälla alla människor, oavsett var man råkar leva.
name: Humanisterna Syd
organizer.name: Martin Karlsson

category.name: religion/beliefs
description:
Welcome to Stockholm Skeptic Discussions!

PLEASE NOTE: Skepticism doesn't mean being arbitrary "sceptical". A skeptic, or "freethinker" is one who prefers beliefs and conclusions that are reliable and valid to ones that are personally comforting or convenient (such as religion, conspiracy theories, alternative medicine, spiritual healing or anything "supernatural"). Skepticism is not an ideology or a belief system. Skepticism is a methodology for learning about and understanding the world based on the scientific method. To learn more, please watch this short video: "What is a Skeptic?", and preferably also "Why people believe weird things", both by Michael Shermer of The Sceptic Society (USA).

This group is for people who want to discuss and learn about the world in accordance to this methodology (including, but not limited to conversations about science, pseudo-science, philosophy, atheism, secular ethics, evolution and humanism) with like-minded people in the Stockholm area. 

No merits are required apart from respecting that. We all have to start somewhere :)

Hope to see you there!

PS: If you want to read more, and better understand terminology we may use on the meetups, we have more resources and links listed here.

Rules: Don't be condescending or otherwise aggressive. A necessary part of being a skeptic is questioning your own stances, being able to handle critique and letting others speak. Even if you're "sure" you're right (which you shouldn't be), we are not organizing these events to listen to someone's agenda. We're here to participate in discussions where scientific and rational arguments trumps attitude. Sexism and racism also is strictly forbidden.
name: Stockholm Skeptic Discussions

In this way, we will not be promoting or privileging one interpretation or worldview over another, instead, we'll be looking for common bridges across religions and worldviews in order to positively impact our personal life and society through a universal spiritual revolution.

category.name: religion/beliefs
description:
This is a group with focus on the real world. That will produce a dictionary to use when you want to call things for what they are. That help you root out all those words with religious connotations from your language.

Why give religion credibility by using words that carry their agenda? Isn’t it about time you stop doing that?

Take the expression 'to desecrate' for example. It is said that you can do this to a church. Which is strange. Because if you piss you piss. Right? No matter if it’s on Skatteverket, a church or Trump Tower. Desecrate? Yeah yeah… Or look at the word soul. Please define it. Do you find it difficult? Well, I say it’s since it’s concocted. Fiction. Made up. And what is holy really? Join and let’s find out!
name: Secular Dictionary Production With Big Mary
organizer.name: Jan Åhlander

description:
This is a group with focus on the real world. That will produce a dictionary to use when you want to call things for what they are. That help you root out all those words with religious connotations from your language.

Why give religion credibility by using words that carry their agenda? Isn’t it about time you stop doing that?

Take the expression 'to desecrate' for example. It is said that you can do this to a church. Which is strange. Because if you piss you piss. Right? No matter if it’s on Skatteverket, a church or Trump Tower. Desecrate? Yeah yeah… Or look at the word soul. Please define it. Do you find it difficult? Well, I say it’s since it’s concocted. Fiction. Made up. And what is holy really? Join and let’s find out!
name: Secular Dictionary Production With Big Mary

category.name: religion/beliefs
description:
Open for everyone that feels like there could be more to life than just what our eyes can see and our minds contemplate! Starting sometime in February or march - We will do a course that will run for 7 weeks from our home in Kärrtorp, exploring life through the christian faith. We aim to host it in a low-key easy style; where no questions are considered in appropriate and no one should feel unwelcomed.

The outline of the course is as follows:
Session 1 The Good God
Session 2 The Trustworthy God
Session 3 The Generous God
Session 4 The Liberating God
Session 5 The Fulfilling God
Session 6 The Life-Giving God
Session 7 The Joyful God

Welcome - wether saint, heretic, skeptic, seeker, agnostic or believer... every one can come no matter where you are on your spiritual journey!
Peace & Love: Anna & Samuel

-------

Öppen för alla som känner att det kan vara mer till livet än vad våra ögon kan se och våra förstånd säger oss! Med början någon gång i februari eller mars - kommer vi att göra en 7 veckors kurs i vårt hem i Kärrtorp, som utforskar livet genom den kristna tron. Vi strävar efter att skapa en enkel, avskalad plats; där inga frågor anses olämpliga och ingen ska känna sig ovälkommen.

Kursens upplägg:
Session 1 Den goda Guden
Session 2 Den trovärdiga Guden
Session 3 Den generösa Guden
Session 4 Den befriande Guden
Session 5 Den uppfyllande Guden
Session 6 Den livgivande Guden
Session 7 Den glädjande Guden

Oavsett var du befinner dig på din livsresa - om du är sökare, troende, skeptiker, heretiker eller ett helgon, så är du varmt välkommen!
Fred & kärlek / Anna & Samuel

category.name: religion/beliefs
description:
Welcome to Stockholm Skeptic Discussions!

PLEASE NOTE: Skepticism doesn't mean being arbitrary "sceptical". A skeptic, or "freethinker" is one who prefers beliefs and conclusions that are reliable and valid to ones that are personally comforting or convenient (such as religion, conspiracy theories, alternative medicine, spiritual healing or anything "supernatural"). Skepticism is not an ideology or a belief system. Skepticism is a methodology for learning about and understanding the world based on the scientific method. To learn more, please watch this short video: "What is a Skeptic?", and preferably also "Why people believe weird things", both by Michael Shermer of The Sceptic Society (USA).

This group is for people who want to discuss and learn about the world in accordance to this methodology (including, but not limited to conversations about science, pseudo-science, philosophy, atheism, secular ethics, evolution and humanism) with like-minded people in the Stockholm area. 

No merits are required apart from respecting that. We all have to start somewhere :)

Hope to see you there!

PS: If you want to read more, and better understand terminology we may use on the meetups, we have more resources and links listed here.

Rules: Don't be condescending or otherwise aggressive. A necessary part of being a skeptic is questioning your own stances, being able to handle critique and letting others speak. Even if you're "sure" you're right (which you shouldn't be), we are not organizing these events to listen to someone's agenda. We're here to participate in discussions where scientific and rational arguments trumps attitude. Sexism and racism also is strictly forbidden.

category.name: religion/beliefs
description:
Welcome to Stockholm Skeptic Discussions!

PLEASE NOTE: Skepticism doesn't mean being arbitrary "sceptical". A skeptic, or "freethinker" is one who prefers beliefs and conclusions that are reliable and valid to ones that are personally comforting or convenient (such as religion, conspiracy theories, alternative medicine, spiritual healing or anything "supernatural"). Skepticism is not an ideology or a belief system. Skepticism is a methodology for learning about and understanding the world based on the scientific method. To learn more, please watch this short video: "What is a Skeptic?", and preferably also "Why people believe weird things", both by Michael Shermer of The Sceptic Society (USA).

This group is for people who want to discuss and learn about the world in accordance to this methodology (including, but not limited to conversations about science, pseudo-science, philosophy, atheism, secular ethics, evolution and humanism) with like-minded people in the Stockholm area. 

No merits are required apart from respecting that. We all have to start somewhere :)

Hope to see you there!

PS: If you want to read more, and better understand terminology we may use on the meetups, we have more resources and links listed here.

Rules: Don't be condescending or otherwise aggressive. A necessary part of being a skeptic is questioning your own stances, being able to handle critique and letting others speak. Even if you're "sure" you're right (which you shouldn't be), we are not organizing these events to listen to someone's agenda. We're here to participate in discussions where scientific and rational arguments trumps attitude. Sexism and racism also is strictly forbidden.

description:
This is a group with focus on the real world. That will produce a dictionary to use when you want to call things for what they are. That help you root out all those words with religious connotations from your language.

Why give religion credibility by using words that carry their agenda? Isn’t it about time you stop doing that?

Take the expression 'to desecrate' for example. It is said that you can do this to a church. Which is strange. Because if you piss you piss. Right? No matter if it’s on Skatteverket, a church or Trump Tower. Desecrate? Yeah yeah… Or look at the word soul. Please define it. Do you find it difficult? Well, I say it’s since it’s concocted. Fiction. Made up. And what is holy really? Join and let’s find out!
name: Secular Dictionary Production With Big Mary

category.name: religion/beliefs
description:
Open for everyone that feels like there could be more to life than just what our eyes can see and our minds contemplate! Starting sometime in February or march - We will do a course that will run for 7 weeks from our home in Kärrtorp, exploring life through the christian faith. We aim to host it in a low-key easy style; where no questions are considered in appropriate and no one should feel unwelcomed.

The outline of the course is as follows:
Session 1 The Good God
Session 2 The Trustworthy God
Session 3 The Generous God
Session 4 The Liberating God
Session 5 The Fulfilling God
Session 6 The Life-Giving God
Session 7 The Joyful God

Welcome - wether saint, heretic, skeptic, seeker, agnostic or believer... every one can come no matter where you are on your spiritual journey!
Peace & Love: Anna & Samuel

-------

Öppen för alla som känner att det kan vara mer till livet än vad våra ögon kan se och våra förstånd säger oss! Med början någon gång i februari eller mars - kommer vi att göra en 7 veckors kurs i vårt hem i Kärrtorp, som utforskar livet genom den kristna tron. Vi strävar efter att skapa en enkel, avskalad plats; där inga frågor anses olämpliga och ingen ska känna sig ovälkommen.

Kursens upplägg:
Session 1 Den goda Guden
Session 2 Den trovärdiga Guden
Session 3 Den generösa Guden
Session 4 Den befriande Guden
Session 5 Den uppfyllande Guden
Session 6 Den livgivande Guden
Session 7 Den glädjande Guden

Oavsett var du befinner dig på din livsresa - om du är sökare, troende, skeptiker, heretiker eller ett helgon, så är du varmt välkommen!
Fred & kärlek / Anna & Samuel

category.name: religion/beliefs
description:
Open for everyone that feels like there could be more to life than just what our eyes can see and our minds contemplate! Starting sometime in February or march - We will do a course that will run for 7 weeks from our home in Kärrtorp, exploring life through the christian faith. We aim to host it in a low-key easy style; where no questions are considered in appropriate and no one should feel unwelcomed.

The outline of the course is as follows:
Session 1 The Good God
Session 2 The Trustworthy God
Session 3 The Generous God
Session 4 The Liberating God
Session 5 The Fulfilling God
Session 6 The Life-Giving God
Session 7 The Joyful God

Welcome - wether saint, heretic, skeptic, seeker, agnostic or believer... every one can come no matter where you are on your spiritual journey!
Peace & Love: Anna & Samuel

-------

Öppen för alla som känner att det kan vara mer till livet än vad våra ögon kan se och våra förstånd säger oss! Med början någon gång i februari eller mars - kommer vi att göra en 7 veckors kurs i vårt hem i Kärrtorp, som utforskar livet genom den kristna tron. Vi strävar efter att skapa en enkel, avskalad plats; där inga frågor anses olämpliga och ingen ska känna sig ovälkommen.

Kursens upplägg:
Session 1 Den goda Guden
Session 2 Den trovärdiga Guden
Session 3 Den generösa Guden
Session 4 Den befriande Guden
Session 5 Den uppfyllande Guden
Session 6 Den livgivande Guden
Session 7 Den glädjande Guden

Oavsett var du befinner dig på din livsresa - om du är sökare, troende, skeptiker, heretiker eller ett helgon, så är du varmt välkommen!
Fred & kärlek / Anna & Samuel

category.name: religion/beliefs
description:
Welcome to Stockholm Skeptic Discussions!

PLEASE NOTE: Skepticism doesn't mean being arbitrary "sceptical". A skeptic, or "freethinker" is one who prefers beliefs and conclusions that are reliable and valid to ones that are personally comforting or convenient (such as religion, conspiracy theories, alternative medicine, spiritual healing or anything "supernatural"). Skepticism is not an ideology or a belief system. Skepticism is a methodology for learning about and understanding the world based on the scientific method. To learn more, please watch this short video: "What is a Skeptic?", and preferably also "Why people believe weird things", both by Michael Shermer of The Sceptic Society (USA).

This group is for people who want to discuss and learn about the world in accordance to this methodology (including, but not limited to conversations about science, pseudo-science, philosophy, atheism, secular ethics, evolution and humanism) with like-minded people in the Stockholm area. 

No merits are required apart from respecting that. We all have to start somewhere :)

Hope to see you there!

PS: If you want to read more, and better understand terminology we may use on the meetups, we have more resources and links listed here.

Rules: Don't be condescending or otherwise aggressive. A necessary part of being a skeptic is questioning your own stances, being able to handle critique and letting others speak. Even if you're "sure" you're right (which you shouldn't be), we are not organizing these events to listen to someone's agenda. We're here to participate in discussions where scientific and rational arguments trumps attitude. Sexism and racism also is strictly forbidden.

description:
This is a group with focus on the real world. That will produce a dictionary to use when you want to call things for what they are. That help you root out all those words with religious connotations from your language.

Why give religion credibility by using words that carry their agenda? Isn’t it about time you stop doing that?

Take the expression 'to desecrate' for example. It is said that you can do this to a church. Which is strange. Because if you piss you piss. Right? No matter if it’s on Skatteverket, a church or Trump Tower. Desecrate? Yeah yeah… Or look at the word soul. Please define it. Do you find it difficult? Well, I say it’s since it’s concocted. Fiction. Made up. And what is holy really? Join and let’s find out!

description:
This is a group with focus on the real world. That will produce a dictionary to use when you want to call things for what they are. That help you root out all those words with religious connotations from your language.

Why give religion credibility by using words that carry their agenda? Isn’t it about time you stop doing that?

Take the expression 'to desecrate' for example. It is said that you can do this to a church. Which is strange. Because if you piss you piss. Right? No matter if it’s on Skatteverket, a church or Trump Tower. Desecrate? Yeah yeah… Or look at the word soul. Please define it. Do you find it difficult? Well, I say it’s since it’s concocted. Fiction. Made up. And what is holy really? Join and let’s find out!
name: Secular Dictionary Production With Big Mary

category.name: religion/beliefs
description:
Open for everyone that feels like there could be more to life than just what our eyes can see and our minds contemplate! Starting sometime in February or march - We will do a course that will run for 7 weeks from our home in Kärrtorp, exploring life through the christian faith. We aim to host it in a low-key easy style; where no questions are considered in appropriate and no one should feel unwelcomed.

The outline of the course is as follows:
Session 1 The Good God
Session 2 The Trustworthy God
Session 3 The Generous God
Session 4 The Liberating God
Session 5 The Fulfilling God
Session 6 The Life-Giving God
Session 7 The Joyful God

Welcome - wether saint, heretic, skeptic, seeker, agnostic or believer... every one can come no matter where you are on your spiritual journey!
Peace & Love: Anna & Samuel

-------

Öppen för alla som känner att det kan vara mer till livet än vad våra ögon kan se och våra förstånd säger oss! Med början någon gång i februari eller mars - kommer vi att göra en 7 veckors kurs i vårt hem i Kärrtorp, som utforskar livet genom den kristna tron. Vi strävar efter att skapa en enkel, avskalad plats; där inga frågor anses olämpliga och ingen ska känna sig ovälkommen.

Kursens upplägg:
Session 1 Den goda Guden
Session 2 Den trovärdiga Guden
Session 3 Den generösa Guden
Session 4 Den befriande Guden
Session 5 Den uppfyllande Guden
Session 6 Den livgivande Guden
Session 7 Den glädjande Guden

Oavsett var du befinner dig på din livsresa - om du är sökare, troende, skeptiker, heretiker eller ett helgon, så är du varmt välkommen!
Fred & kärlek / Anna & Samuel
name: Life & Jesus Explored - Stockholm

description: Humanisterna Syd är en lokalavdelning inom förbundet Humanisterna som geografiskt omfattar Skåne och Blekinge. Vi anordnar medlemsaktiviteter som föreläsningar, debatter, diskussions- och pubkvällar. För kontakt, maila oss på syd@humanisterna.se Förbundet Humanisterna vill främja humanismens livssyn som idé- och värdegrund för samhälle, kultur och etik. Grundläggande för humanismen är kritiskt tänkande och en vetenskaplig kunskapssyn. Humanismen är en sekulär – icke-religiös – livssyn som anser att det inte finns några förnuftiga skäl att tro på religiösa dogmer, gudar eller övernaturliga förklaringar av tillvaron. Humanismen sätter människan och människovärdet i centrum. Den förenar medmänsklighet och förnuft i en strävan att skapa ett bättre samhälle, där ansvaret läggs på människan själv. Demokrati och mänskliga rättigheter är universella värden som måste gälla alla människor, oavsett var man råkar leva.
name: Humanisterna Syd
